        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 1:43PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 143 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Buffalo Ridge, or near Stuart, moving southeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Rocky Mount...
Stuart...
Ferrum...
Penhook...
Ararat...
Bassett...
and Sydnorsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
